This recipe was really good, but if the tomatoes are not really in-season flavorful, try roasting them with a drizzle of balsamic vinegar. They added alot of flavor to the stacks, and the presentation was beautiful! I also cut the polenta with a small serrated edge biscuit cutter to make them look more special.

