This dish definitely needs twice the polenta - there's an error there. Otherwise, if you use fresh ingredients, this was a great recipe!

Rating: 3
The basil in the polenta is delicious. Something is strange with the directions though -- if you cut the polenta in 25 pieces from a 9x9 pan, those will be some tiny squares. Cut it to fit the eggplant you have. I made two minor modifications to the recipe: Instead of mozarella, I used a very mild, white colby grated fine. Then I really "stacked" the layers, using two layers of each, polenta, eggplant, tomato, and cheese ... then repeated. Served with a baby romaine salad this was a sensational summer dinner. All the ingredients where fresh from my local farmers market. My husband called it "rich man's pizza." I'll serve this again.

Rating: 4
I made this recipe for a dinner party, and it was a huge hit. I used pre-prepared polenta which you just have to slice. The stacks did not want to stay upright when the cheese was melting, so the presentation was not as pretty on some as on others, but it was very tasty.

